git init
--This command initializes a new Git repository in the current folder.
--It creates a hidden .git directory that stores all version control information.


get status
--Gives the information of the current state of the git repo

git branch
--This command is used to view or create branches.

To create a new branch:

--git branch dev

This creates a branch named dev but does not switch to it.

git checkout -b <branch name>
--Switching to new branch if you want to switch to an existing branch then use git checkout branch with -b
When you do not want to affect your actual/main code, you create a separate branch.

Equivalent to:

git branch dev
git checkout dev

Output:

Switched to a new branch 'dev'

--git checkout -b master
Switched to a new branch 'master'

--git add <file name>   
This command adds the file test.py to the Git staging area.
It means Git will now track the changes made in test.py for the next commit.
it will use to stage untracked file


after deleting 
it will deleted from system but not from git
so restore it whenever you need using..

git restore --staged <file name>
--used to untracked/tracked the staged file



git branch
--gives the info / list all the branches in git repo

git commit -m "<your message>"
--Used to track the staged files after being added by git add


git clone <repository-url>
--git clone is used to copy/download an existing remote Git repository to your local system.

In your local you did git init and get repository what is the by default branch name--->master
and when you use git clone or github at that time by default branch name is ---main


git push origin main
--Pushes your local commits from the main branch to the remote repository (usually GitHub).

git push → upload changes
origin → remote repository name
main → branch name

git remote -v
--Shows the remote repository URLs connected to your project.
eg:
origin  https://github.com/user/project.git (fetch)
origin  https://github.com/user/project.git (push)

git pull origin main
--Downloads the latest changes from the remote main branch and merges them into your local branch.
git pull → fetch + merge

